    "note": "Benign autosomal recessive disorder causing conjugated hyperbilirubinemia due to defective hepatic storage of bilirubin. Caused by mutations in SLCO1B1 and SLCO1B3 genes affecting OATP1B1 and OATP1B3 transport proteins. Mild jaundice with elevated coproporphyrin I and normal liver function. No treatment needed. Important to distinguish from Dubin-Johnson syndrome and obstructive jaundice.",
